<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="376" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,632,983]" pageId="9" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,885,911]" pageId="9" pageNumber="376">Remarks</emphasis>
. Present materials agree well with redescribtion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peart" authorityYear="2007" box="[896,1000,885,911]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampithoidae" genus="Cymadusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setosa">
<emphasis box="[896,1000,885,911]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="376">C. setosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peart, R. A." box="[1045,1189,885,911]" pageId="9" pageNumber="376" pagination="301 - 336" refId="ref5828" refString="Peart, R. A. (2004) A revision of the Cymadusa filosa complex (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Corophioidea: Ampithoidae). Journal of Natural History, 38, 301 - 336. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 0022293021000055441" type="journal article" year="2004">Peart (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. Other records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peart" authorityYear="2007" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampithoidae" genus="Cymadusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="376">Cymadusa setosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Persian Gulf are from 
<collectingCountry box="[645,727,920,946]" name="Kuwait" pageId="9" pageNumber="376">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
waters by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, D. A." box="[851,997,920,947]" pageId="9" pageNumber="376" refId="ref4893" refString="Jones, D. A. (1986) A Field Guide to the Sea Shores of Kuwait and the Arabian Gulf. Universty of Kuwait, Distributed Blandford Press, Kuwait City, 192 pp." type="book" year="1986">Jones (1986)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ali, M. &amp; Al-Ghunaim, A. &amp; Subrahmanyam, M. N. V. &amp; Al-Enezi, Y. &amp; Al-Said, T. &amp; Al-Zakri, W. &amp; Grintsov, V. A." box="[1008,1191,920,947]" pageId="9" pageNumber="376" pagination="767 - 819" refId="ref4180" refString="Ali, M., Al-Ghunaim, A., Subrahmanyam, M. N. V., Al-Enezi, Y., Al-Said, T., Al-Zakri, W. &amp; Grintsov, V. A. (2018) On the diversity of amphipods inhabiting Sargassum as well as clear areas in Kuwait coastal waters, with an assessment of the effect of turbidity and notes on their abundance, composition, and distribution: a preliminary study. Crustaceana, 91 (7), 767 - 819. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 15685403 - 00003799" type="journal article" year="2018">
Ali 
<emphasis box="[1051,1100,920,946]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="376">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Al-Yamani, F. Y. &amp; Al-Kandari, M. &amp; Polikarpov, I. &amp; Grintsov, V." pageId="9" pageNumber="376" refId="ref4286" refString="Al-Yamani, F. Y., Al-Kandari, M., Polikarpov, I. &amp; Grintsov, V. (2019) Field Guide of Order Amphipoda (Malacostraca, Crustacea) of Kuwait. Kuwait Institute for Scientific Research, Kuwait, 388 pp." type="book" year="2019">
Al-Yamani 
